article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 70, Texas Wesleyan 54
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Forward Travis Gabbidon's double-double helped lead Texas-San Antonio to a 70-54 victory over Texas Wesleyan on Wednesday night. Gabbidon scored 21 points and pulled down 14 rebounds for the Roadrunners (5-4). Isaiah Allen scored 12 points and Joey Shank added 10 points for Texas-San Antonio. Fred Eshon led Texas Wesleyan (7-5) with 13 points. Dane Dmitrovic added 11 points for the Rams. The Rams led by a point midway through the first half before the Roadrunners used a nine-point run to go ahead 23-15. Texas San Antonio led the rest of the way. Texas Wesleyan shot 50 percent from the field in the first half but hit only 36 percent in the second half. Texas-San Antonio shot 45 percent from the field for the game.
